    "attributes": {
        "action": "Drop unnecessary plans for a deeply damaging switch \r\nfrom the CE to UK CA mark",
        "additional_details": "In the modern world, many essential or otherwise important systems, from escalators, vehicles, air conditioning, even power grid infrastructure etc are built up from a plethora of individual sub-systems and components.  The proposed rapid rewrite in the rules of safety certification for all future replacements - without any chance for regulatory and industry bodies to react will seed unimaginable chaos.\r\n",
        "background": "The CE mark already exists, the costs and benfits of compliance are already sunk / won.  Adding an extra layer of unprofitable red tape, just for the sake of it - is illogical, destructive and creates no benefit.",
